snippet.textDisplay:
The song starts beautifully, with a bang. It attracts attention of the listener, and then Zeb cutely keeps the interest going on with her lines, ending on a high note as the mukhada ends. The mandolin is a melodious filler, and fills the gap before the antara. Zeb takes it over again in the antara on a playful note. Till the first antara, the song goes on well, but then, in the ending part, the song fizzles out and one is waiting for it to end. The part where 'megha barse rim jhim' would have been tackled in a better way. The song attains a last high point at the end, which is again a treat to the ears.
The best song in this episode of Coke studio. Waiting for more to come.
